OL,3,CAccountability gaps amid 'rising anti-
OL,4,Cmigrant sentiment', report finds
OL,6,FDr Joseph's report also finds that
OL,7,Fstructural and intersectional racism
OL,8,Fpersists, with significant disparities
OL,9,Fin employment and education outcomes.
OL,11,FShe says that hate speech legislation
OL,12,Fremains outdated and that data
OL,13,Fcollection on racism and ethnicity
OL,14,Fremains insufficient.
OL,16,FOne of the other key findings is that
OL,17,F"rising anti-migrant sentiment and far-
OL,18,Fright activity pose increasing risks
OL,19,Fto social cohesion".
